    • removedFromMergedRegion

      protected void removedFromMergedRegion()
      This method is called when a cell is removed from a merged region. It sets the logicalCell property of the cell to itself, and sets the horizontal and vertical spans to 1. This method is typically called internally when a merged region is unmerged or when a cell is updated in a merged region.

    • getLogicalAbstractCell

      protected final C getLogicalAbstractCell()

      the logical abstract cell of type C associated with this cell

      protected abstract AbstractWorkbook<S,R,C> getAbstractWorkbook()

      the associated abstract workbook of type AbstractWorkbook<S, R, C> providing access to the workbook operations and metadata
